This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the stochastic variance-reduced gradient method and its accelerated variant, which are commonly used in training supervised machine learning models. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as machine learning is a subfield of AI. Additionally, the paper may be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a new algorithmic approach to the existing methods. It may also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the methods discussed are commonly used in training neural networks. Finally, it may be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as machine learning is often used in computer vision applications.
